TY  - JOUR
AU  - Chen, Huafeng (Jason)
AU  - Chen, Jason V
AU  - Li, Feng
AU  - Li, Pengfei
T1  - Measuring Operating Leverage
PY  - 2022
Y1  - 2022/03/01
DO  - 10.1093/rapstu/raab025
JO  - The Review of Asset Pricing Studies
JA  - Rev Asset Pric Stud
VL  - 12
IS  - 1
SP  - 112
EP  - 154
SN  - 2045-9920
AB  - We examine a simple measure of operating leverage: the ratio of fixed costs (measured by depreciation and amortization plus selling, general, and administrative expenses) to the market (or book) value of assets. We find that this measure of operating leverage positively predicts returns. This operating leverage measure is not explained by common factors and performs better than the traditional measures of operating leverage. Furthermore, an exploratory two-factor model with the operating leverage factor works at least as well as, but does not subsume, the Fama and French five-factor model. (JEL G11, G12, G30)
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rapstu/raab025
ER  - 



